        <bioghist id="ref2">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Francis Long enlisted in the United States Navy in 1943. He went to Newport, RI for basic training, and then was transferred to Norfolk, VA, while his crew waited for their ship (USS Wasp) to be finished. Long's crew shipped to the Pacific Theatre via Hawaii. They encountered many naval battles in the Pacific, and in one battle, their ship was bombed, and suffered a great deal of damage, along with the loss of almost 300 soldiers. Due to the damage on the ship, they had to sail back to Hawaii for repairs. When the ships repairs were completed they sailed for Japan, and when the shore was in sight, it was announced that the Atomic bomb had been dropped and the fighting was over.</p>
        </bioghist>
